the zero-length string.

variables.name: PRAVAIL-MIB::pravailTrapDetail

description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed
node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified
domain name. If the name is unknown, the value is
the zero-length string.
variables.name: SNMPv2-MIB::sysName

description: Temporary string for reporting information in traps
variables.name: PRAVAIL-MIB::pravailTrapString

description: Temporary string for reporting additional detail (if any)
about a trap
variables.name: PRAVAIL-MIB::pravailTrapDetail

description: The user who made the change, or 'system' if it is a system-
generated change.
variables.name: PRAVAIL-MIB::pravailUsername

description: The sub-system that made the change. Examples of the sub-
systems that can make changes include: ATLAS, CLI, deployment
diagnostics, file system, mitigation, notifications, system
and user accounts.
variables.name: PRAVAIL-MIB::pravailSubsystem

description: The setting type to which the change corresponds. For example
the name of a protection group if it is a protection group
change or the name of a server type if it is a server type
change.
variables.name: PRAVAIL-MIB::pravailSettingType
